A 65-year-old randy night guard, Oluwole Akinola, who allegedly abducted two minors for days and sexually assaulted them while they were in his custody, has been arrested in Ilorin by the Kwara State Command of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, NSCDC. Spokesman of the NSCDC in the state, Babawale Zaid Afolabi, who confirmed the incident to newsmen in Ilorin on Wednesday disclosed that “the Gender– based Violence Unit of the Corps is currently interrogating the suspect while the two victims are also helping in the investigation.” The spokesman recalled that one of the victim’s father, Borokini Oluwaseun, 32, of Aduralere Street, Ilorin, complained at the NSCDC office that his12 years old daughter Semilore who has been declared missing for some days was found in the custody of one Akinola Oluwole, 65, who lives in Shao garage area of the metropolis. He revealed further that the timely arrival of the NSCDC operatives saved the suspect from mob action as the people of the neighbourhood insisted that it was not the first time Oluwole would be accused of rape and sexual molestation of minors. In his preliminary statement, the suspect, who claimed to have lost his wive 15 years ago, “denied having sexually assaulted the minors adding that the two girls actually approached him to shelter them and he did not sleep with them but harboured them for days.” The state commandant, Iskil Makinde Iskil Ayinla, has ordered the two minors to undergo further medical examination while the case be transferred to the Gender- based violence unit of the corps for proper investigation and possible prosecution of the suspect.